{
    "publish_date": "2013-03-14T08:01:14.000Z", 
    "score": 0.00011696248428316618, 
    "video_length": "PT6M28S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 1: To celebrate the\nmathematical constant of pi,", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "0.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re going to attempt the most\naccurate calculation ever", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "2.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of pi using pies.", 
            "dur": "3.02", 
            "start": "6.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, before we do our pie-based\npi calculation,", 
            "dur": "3.009", 
            "start": "13.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;ll have a quick crash course\nin circles and why pi", 
            "dur": "3.591", 
            "start": "16.309"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so important.", 
            "dur": "0.6", 
            "start": "19.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now to do that because we&#39;re in\nthe UK, home of many famous", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "20.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "circles, we&#39;ve come from the\noldest and greatest circles,", 
            "dur": "3.2", 
            "start": "24.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is, of course, this one.", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "27.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s the football circle here at\nKnott County Football Club.", 
            "dur": "4.33", 
            "start": "29.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Apparently, they are\nthe world&#39;s oldest", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "33.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Football League club.", 
            "dur": "1.453", 
            "start": "36.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 2: How do\nyou know that?", 
            "dur": "0.967", 
            "start": "37.493"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 1: There&#39;s a giant\nsign that says that", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "38.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "right behind me.", 
            "dur": "0.855", 
            "start": "39.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which does mean for a while\nthere, I guess they had no one", 
            "dur": "2.255", 
            "start": "40.435"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "else to play, but who knows.", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "42.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this circle here, as you can\nsee, there&#39;s two things", 
            "dur": "3.34", 
            "start": "45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "going on with the circle.", 
            "dur": "1.16", 
            "start": "48.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First of all, there\nis the diameter.", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "49.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it&#39;s this nice, wonderful\nstraight line here that goes", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "51.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "right through the middle\nof the circle.", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "55.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the great thing about\ndiameter is it&#39;s a nice", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "56.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "straight line.", 
            "dur": "1.52", 
            "start": "59.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if I wanted to, I could get\na measuring tape, and I could", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "60.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "measure from the start all the\nway across here to the finish", 
            "dur": "3.07", 
            "start": "63.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and get a very precise\nmeasurement of the distance", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "66.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "across the circle.", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "69.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now around here, we have\nthe circumference.", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "70.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now this is a lot harder\nto measure.", 
            "dur": "4.26", 
            "start": "73.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As you can see, it&#39;s\na curved line.", 
            "dur": "2.03", 
            "start": "77.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So instead of having\nto measure it", 
            "dur": "1.37", 
            "start": "79.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "directly, we can use pi.", 
            "dur": "2.23", 
            "start": "80.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now pi is the ratio of the\nstraight line diameter to the", 
            "dur": "3.88", 
            "start": "83.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "total distance all the way\naround the outside.", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "86.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if we know that ratio, we\ncan do one measurement for the", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "89.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "diameter, multiply it by pi, and\nget the exact distance all", 
            "dur": "5.01", 
            "start": "92.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the way around the outside.", 
            "dur": "1.72", 
            "start": "97.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "All right, enough messing around\non a football pitch--", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "99.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let&#39;s go get our pies out.", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "102.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "All right, first thing\nwe need is a circle.", 
            "dur": "3.9", 
            "start": "104.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 2: People find\nit notoriously", 
            "dur": "1.01", 
            "start": "108.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hard to draw circles.", 
            "dur": "1.09", 
            "start": "109.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How do you get around\nthis problem?", 
            "dur": "2.005", 
            "start": "110.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 1: Actually, we were\ntalking to the guy who does", 
            "dur": "2.255", 
            "start": "112.345"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the circle on the pitch for\nthe football stadium here.", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "114.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he does it the same way,\nI think, most people do.", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "117.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He gets a bit of string, makes\nthe middle bit of the string", 
            "dur": "3.48", 
            "start": "119.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "remain perfectly still in what\nwill become the center of the", 
            "dur": "2.19", 
            "start": "123.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "circle, and then use that to\ndraw a nice, equal distance", 
            "dur": "3.53", 
            "start": "125.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "line all the way around.", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "128.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, I guess that&#39;s the best\nway to define a circle--", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "130.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s the line of all the points\nthe same distance away", 
            "dur": "3.06", 
            "start": "132.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from a center point.", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "135.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The center point will\nbe my pen, and the", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "138.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "outside will be the chalk.", 
            "dur": "1.27", 
            "start": "140.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "All right.", 
            "dur": "1.504", 
            "start": "159.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s do this.", 
            "dur": "1.676", 
            "start": "160.744"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My goal is to not actually do\nany measurements other than", 
            "dur": "3.6", 
            "start": "162.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "using pies.", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "166.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the entire thing is going\nto be pie-based.", 
            "dur": "1.426", 
            "start": "167.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We get the circumference and the\nexact number of pies, give", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "171.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or take, we get the diameter and\nnumber of pies, divide one", 
            "dur": "3.53", 
            "start": "174.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by the other, we get pi.", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "178.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Pi was historically really\ncalculated this way because", 
            "dur": "4.58", 
            "start": "184.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s notoriously inaccurate\nto try and calculate pi by", 
            "dur": "7.97", 
            "start": "189.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "measuring a circle.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "197.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To get any kind of accuracy on\nour final answer, we have to", 
            "dur": "3.27", 
            "start": "220.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be as precise as we can be.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "223.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is a mild problem because\nI want to go through from the", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "235.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "very edge of the circle, but,\nas you can see, I&#39;ve", 
            "dur": "1.94", 
            "start": "238.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "positioned all the pies exactly\non the line as if", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "240.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they&#39;re little mini tangents.", 
            "dur": "1.68", 
            "start": "242.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m going to have to move\nthese two out, and then I can", 
            "dur": "3.39", 
            "start": "244.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "start doing the diameter exactly\non the circumference", 
            "dur": "4.605", 
            "start": "247.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there like that.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "252.175"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that&#39;s 84 and 1/3.", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "271"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "264 and 2/3 pies around, where\nthe diameter is 84 and 1/3 pi.", 
            "dur": "6.3", 
            "start": "274.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To get pi, we just divide the\ncircumference by the diameter.", 
            "dur": "4.26", 
            "start": "280.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, and if we actually work out\nwhat that is, it equals--", 
            "dur": "2.97", 
            "start": "284.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s pretty good.", 
            "dur": "1.292", 
            "start": "291.028"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Pi from pies, we got 3.13834,\nwhich is approximately 3.14.", 
            "dur": "12.36", 
            "start": "292.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So using pies, we&#39;ve\ngot pi to be 3.14.", 
            "dur": "6.295", 
            "start": "304.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I am a very happy\nman right now.", 
            "dur": "3.595", 
            "start": "310.975"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anything between 3.1 and 3.2,\nI would have been happy.", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "314.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But to get 3.14, I&#39;m\ndownright ecstatic.", 
            "dur": "3.275", 
            "start": "317.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there you are.", 
            "dur": "0.859", 
            "start": "320.855"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is officially the world&#39;s\nmost accurate calculation of", 
            "dur": "4.646", 
            "start": "321.714"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pi using pies.", 
            "dur": "4.81", 
            "start": "326.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 2: It wasn&#39;t really\nsomething we planned to make", 
            "dur": "1.633", 
            "start": "331.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "part of the video, but as a\nlot of you have asked, the", 
            "dur": "2.947", 
            "start": "332.803"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pies we used were donated and\nwere no longer fit for human", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "335.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "consumption.", 
            "dur": "0.89", 
            "start": "339.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we couldn&#39;t give them to\ncharity, like we did, for", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "340.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "example, with all the\nto baked beans that", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "342.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Heinz donated us earlier.", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "345.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "However, in the spirit of pi\nday, we did attempt to make", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "346.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "some kind of gesture, and we\ndonated 314 pounds, of course", 
            "dur": "5.21", 
            "start": "349.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "314, to a local charity here in\nNottingham that helps give", 
            "dur": "4.54", 
            "start": "354.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "food to people in\ntimes of crisis.", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "358.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, a lot of have expressed a\nlot of interest in charity,", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "360.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we&#39;d really encourage you,\nif you&#39;re in a position to do", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "363.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so, to also make a donation.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "366.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we&#39;ve put some links\nunder the video.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "368.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And because we&#39;re all\nnumberphiles here, why not", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "370.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "make your donation a multiple\nof pi in some way?", 
            "dur": "4.35", 
            "start": "372.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SPEAKER 1: 16, 17, 18, this is\nlength L. And that means that", 
            "dur": "5.93", 
            "start": "377.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the distance here is 2L.", 
            "dur": "3.83", 
            "start": "383.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK?", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "387.09"
        }
